- Every exec chain must start from an Event node
- Only use node types and pin names from the reference below

Node Reference — ALWAYS USE EXACT NAME AND PIN NAMES

Node_Type — Valid_Pin_Names

Action — Execute:exec OUT
Branch — Condition:Bool IN, True:exec OUT, False:exec OUT
Event — Event:exec OUT
FlipFlop — Enter:exec IN, Exit:exec OUT, Toggle:Bool OUT
Gate — Enter:exec IN, Open:Bool IN, Exit:exec OUT
ForEachLoop — LoopBody:exec IN, LoopHead:exec OUT, ArrayElement:Data OUT
Gate — Enter:exec IN, Open:Bool IN, Exit:exec OUT
Math — Add:Float IN, Subtract:Float IN, Multiply:Float IN, GreaterThan:Float IN, LessThan:Float IN, Equal:Float IN — Result:Float OUT
Print — Text:String IN — THEN:exec OUT
Set — Target:Object IN, Value:Bool IN — THEN:exec OUT
